<item>
            <title>[OAK-499] SQL-2 query parser doesn&apos;t detect some illegal statements</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-499</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The SQL-2 query parser doesn&apos;t detect some illegal statements, for example&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;select * from [nt:base] where name =+ &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;Hello&apos;&lt;/span&gt;
select * from [nt:base] where name =&amp;gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;Hello&apos;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Both are currently interpreted as &quot;name = &apos;Hello&apos;&quot;, which is wrong.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
